{"favorite_id": 10069, "calc_type": "", "dosing": false, "full_title_en": "Harvey-Bradshaw Index (HBI) for Crohn's Disease", "short_title_en": "Harvey-Bradshaw Index (HBI)", "medium_description_en": "<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-7ecc3e57-d817-3aaa-f8ab-0ccbf78e28f5\">Stratifies severity of Crohn's disease.</span>", "short_description_en": "Crohn's disease severity.", "before_use": "", "instructions_en": "", "purpose_en": ["Prognosis"], "disease_en": ["Inflammatory Bowel Disease", "Crohn's Disease"], "specialty_en": ["Gastroenterology"], "chief_complaint_en": ["Abdominal Mass", "Arthralgia", "Mass", "Fever", "Diarrhea", "Abdominal Pain"], "system_en": ["Gastrointestinal"], "search_abbreviation_en": ["Harvey bradshaw index", "HBI", "CD", "crohns disease", "Crohn's disease", "abdominal mass", "Crohn's disease activity index", "CDAI"], "slug": "harvey-bradshaw-index-hbi-crohns-disease", "seo": {"meta_description_en": "The Harvey-Bradshaw Index (HBI) stratifies severity of Crohn's disease.", "keywords_en": "CD severity, crohns severity, crohns abdominal pain, crohns prognosis, Harvey bradshaw index, HBI, CD, crohns disease, crohn\u2019s disease, abdominal mass, Crohn's disease activity index, CDAI"}, "content": {"how_to_use": {"use_case_en": "", "pearls_pitfalls_en": "", "why_use_en": "<ul>\n<li>Simpler than the <calculator id=\"3318\">CDAI</calculator>, which requires symptoms over the past 7 days.</li>\n<li>Shown to have 93% correlation with the CDAI in the original study (<a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/6102236\" target=\"_blank\">Harvey 1980</a>), a figure&nbsp;that has been duplicated in subsequent studies (<a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/3949241\" target=\"_blank\">Gomes 1986</a>).</li>\n</ul>"}, "next_steps": {"advice_en": "<p>Treatment decisions should be made on the basis of multiple factors, of which disease severity is one.</p>", "management_en": "", "critical_actions_en": ""}, "about": {"formula_en": "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-g